aa(lp317
VOn one of my last visits to Pakistan,
p318
aVI asked Dr. Sono if he would take me
p319
aVto see some of the drip irrigation in the Thar Desert.
p320
aVAnd we left Karachi one morning before dawn.
p321
aVIt was about 115 degrees.
p322
aVAnd we drove for eight hours
p323
aValong this moonscape-like landscape
p324
aVwith very little color, lots of heat,
p325
aVvery little discussion, because we were exhausted.
p326
aa(lp327
VAnd finally, at the end of the journey,
p328
aVI could see this thin little yellow line across the horizon.
p329
aVAnd as we got closer, its significance became apparent.
